                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860N.85/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-31">October 31,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Soviet Ambassador called to see me.</p>
                <p>The Ambassador again undertook a discourse upon the subject of Baltic ships
                    within United States jurisdiction.</p>
                <p>I stated that I would investigate the matter further and would discuss the
                    problem with him once more in an early conversation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
